  <item rdf:about="https://is.enes.org/archive-1/phase-2/documents/milestones/is-enes2_ms2-5_update-of-enes-strategy-for-hpc/view">
    <title>IS-ENES2_MS2.5_Update of ENES strategy for HPC</title>
    <link>https://is.enes.org/archive-1/phase-2/documents/milestones/is-enes2_ms2-5_update-of-enes-strategy-for-hpc/view</link>
    <description>This milestone presents the contribution of the HPC task force to the update of the ENES strategy, focussing on computing issues. To address the challenges faced today by Earth System sciences, the climate modelling community needs to better exploit current and future HPC technologies. This paper lays out an argument to go in that direction following three strands: (i) improving current climate models, while (ii) developing in parallel a new generation of models able and (iii) accessing increased computing capacity including Tier0 platforms. It also describes how new avenues need to be considered regarding people, training and relation with vendors to reach these objectives.</description>
    
    
